 see the core doesn’t include JNDI. Conflicts could arise from dependencies, too.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting Kotlin versions**\\n\\nI see that 3.0.0.RC1 relies on Kotlin 2.1.0, but the test build might be using an older Kotlin plugin. I should check the versions of the libraries to confirm. If the build plugin is below 2.1, testing 3.0 may indeed require updating the Kotlin plugin or dependency.\\n\\nCurrently, the build uses an alias for the Kotlin JVM plugin. I suspect the repository plugin version could be 2.2. I definitely need to inspect this further.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_wIrfwJVE9f9TkwMwSck7EpDK|fc_037b7281c8cc5ca2016a41a995676081938b0cfe975485f063", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"kotlin|kotlin.jvm\" gradle libs.versions.toml settings.gradle build.gradle gradle.properties -S", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2941, "output": 549, "cacheRead": 38912, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42402, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782688137221, "responseId": "resp_037b7281c8cc5ca2016a41a989d5448193bf2435235ef1f436"}}
