ld fail without including hoplite-yaml. I need clarity on this point to move forward effectively.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra deterministic setup is required for hoplite-core. The resolved artifact only depends on Kotlin stdlib/reflect and kotlinx-coroutines, and core coverage is reachable through built-in MapPropertySource, environment/system-property sources, and the built-in .properties parser without Docker, external services, or additional test dependencies.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Hoplite documentation commonly demonstrates YAML/JSON/HOCON/TOML configuration files, but those formats require separate hoplite-* format modules. For hoplite-core tests, use MapPropertySource or built-in .properties support unless intentionally adding coverage for another module.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_037b7281c8cc5ca2016a41a9a0c30c81938e38da36261a9672\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1016, "output": 824, "cacheRead": 41472, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 43312, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782688149690, "responseId": "resp_037b7281c8cc5ca2016a41a996a03c8193b3879b56eccccb3b"}}
